{
  "question_text": "<h3>Split Array with Equal Sum</h3><p>Given an array <code>nums</code>, return <code>true</code> if there are three indices <code>i, j, k</code> such that the sum of four sub-arrays formed by splitting at these indices are equal.</p>",
  "difficulty": "HARD",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Int array nums.",
  "output_format": "bool.",
  "constraints": [
    "n <= 2000"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use prefix sums for efficiency. Pre-calculate prefix sums. Iterate through index $j$ as the middle split. For each $j$, find all possible $i$ that split the left side into two equal sums and store them in a set. Then find if there's any $k$ that splits the right side into two equal sums, both equal to a sum present in the set.",
  "answer": "def splitArray(nums):\n    n = len(nums)\n    if n < 7: return False\n    ps = [0] * (n + 1)\n    for i in range(n): ps[i+1] = ps[i] + nums[i]\n    for j in range(3, n - 3):\n        s = set()\n        for i in range(1, j - 1):\n            if ps[i] == ps[j] - ps[i+1]: s.add(ps[i])\n        for k in range(j + 2, n - 1):\n            if ps[k] - ps[j+1] == ps[n] - ps[k+1] and (ps[k] - ps[j+1]) in s: return True\n    return False",
  "boilerplate": {
    "python": "import sys\nimport json\n\ndef solve(*args):\n    # Implement 548 Split Array with Equal Sum here\n    pass\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    data = sys.stdin.read().strip().split('\\n')\n    if not data or data == ['']: sys.exit(0)\n    args = [json.loads(line) for line in data]\n    print(json.dumps(solve(*args)))",
    "cpp": "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <string>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\nint main() { string line; while (getline(cin, line)) {} return 0; }",
    "java": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.io.*;\npublic class Main {\n    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {\n        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));\n        String line; while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {}\n    }\n}",
